      "problem": "In two test cases, citation placeholders (e.g., '[cite here]') were generated without accompanying PubMed search queries, leaving the user without a path to find the needed references.",
      "root_cause": "Citation recommendation instructions say 'provide PubMed search queries' but this rule is not always enforced when placeholders are generated.",
      "fix": "Add a hard rule: every citation placeholder or recommendation must include at least one specific PubMed search query string. No placeholder without a search path."
    },
    {
      "priority": "P2",
      "title": "No explicit word-count or paragraph-count guidance",
      "observed_in": [],
      "problem": "The skill produces well-structured introduction sections but does not provide guidance on appropriate length for different journal types or manuscript formats.",
      "root_cause": "Writing scope is defined by quality not length.",
      "fix": "Add a brief length guidance note: suggest 300-500 words for most SCI journals, 500-800 for review papers, and indicate that journal-specific instructions override these defaults."
